<section
class="section section-intro section-intro-alt stripe"><div
class="row " ><div
class="medium-12 columns "><p
class="breadcrumbs"><a
href="http://www.kianoff.com">Home</a><a
href="http://www.kianoff.com/about/">About Us</a><span
class="last">Careers</span></p><h1 class="spacebeforelg">Careers Outside Traditional Accounting<small>Put your interest and skills in technology and accounting to work bringing value to our client companies. </small></h1></div></div>
</section>
<main
class="main main-tabs"><div
class="row"><div
class="medium-12 large-8 columns"><div
class="content"><p>
Companies with a mission to survive and flourish in today&rsquo;s marketplace are relying more than ever on technology to help strengthen their performance.</p><p>
As a result, there is a continuing need for experienced consultants - certified professionals with technical skills and broad business experience - to help implement, train and support the accounting and business management systems those companies must use to manage their businesses.</p><h3>
Qualities for Success</h3><p>
Those who are the most successful in this career already have experience with accounting software systems and broad industry background, specifically in areas such as health care, distribution or manufacturing. They enjoy teaching and working one on one with users. Technical skills are also important, including at least an understanding of networks or hands-on development using such tools as SSRS, SQL scripting or .net.</p><h3>
The Kianoff &amp; Associates Mission</h3><p>
At Kianoff &amp; Associates, our consultants work in partnership with system users, administrators and top management at client companies to help them get more from their business systems. Many of our consultants are CPAs or accountants who have also achieved technical certifications such as MCSE. The mission: Help clients improve efficiencies and keep current on new technologies so they can continue to grow and develop their businesses. Our services to clients include business system implementation, training, customizations and report writing, integrations, on-going support and project management.</p><p>
We have clients in a wide variety of industries and businesses, ranging in size from 10 to more than 1,000 employees.&nbsp; We do business with companies throughout Alabama and across the country.</p><p>
Kianoff &amp; Associates is a leading reseller of Microsoft Dynamics GP, Sage 100 <em>(formerly MAS 90 or MAS 200)</em> , Sage 500 <em>(formerly MAS 500)</em> and Intacct accounting and business management systems. We are also certified on Sage CRM and Dynamics&trade;GP CRM.</p><h3>
Join Our Team</h3><p>
Are you motivated by what technology can do to help businesses grow and expand? Are you energized by helping strengthen client&#39;s performance on their systems? Do you have a business or accounting background with experience in our verticals: healthcare, distribution or restaurant/hospitality? If so, tell us about your background in a cover letter and send it, along with your resume, to the address below.</p><p>
<em>Note: We do not accept resumes or applications from employees of companies currently supported by Kianoff and Associates. . &nbsp;</em></p><p>
Resume and cover letter to:&nbsp;<a
href="mailto:info@kianoff.com?subject=Career%20Opportunity">info@kianoff.com</a></p><p>
Or mail to:</p><p>
Kianoff &amp; Associates<br
/>
1128 22nd Street South<br
/>
Birmingham, AL 35205</p><p>
&nbsp;</p><p>
&nbsp;</p></div></div><div
